==English==

===Etymology===
Derived from the Middle English ''iniquite'' which was from the [[Latin]] word ''iniquitas'' from ''iniquus'' which meant [[unjust]] and [[harmful]].

===Noun===
'''iniquity'''
# [[Deviation]] from right, [[wickedness]], [[gross]] [[injustice]].
# A [[wrongful]] act.
# Absence of moral or spiritual values (lawlessness, greek: anomia).
# To deny the [[Sovereignty]] of God.

